  "text": "Microradiographic analysis was done on undecalcified bones that were dehydrated in ethanol and embedded in an epoxy resin [CITATION_1] . 100-200-m sections were generated with a microtome equipped with a rotating diamond knife (model HM3505S; Leica). Contact microradiographs were prepared using an X-ray generator (XRG 3000; Ital Structures), operated at 12 kV and 20 mA for 15 min, and high resolution film (Eastman Kodak Co.). Fixed films were observed with a microscope (Axiophot; Carl Zeiss MicroImaging, Inc.).",
